---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use | AWS Exam Prep"
  description="Terms of use for the AWS certification practice site."
>
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Policy</div>
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      By using this site, you agree to practice responsibly and acknowledge this content is provided
      “as is” without warranty. Always verify against official AWS documentation.
    </p>

    <h2>Allowed Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Personal study and practice for AWS certification exams.</li>
      <li>Non-commercial sharing with attribution via links to this site.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Prohibited</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Redistributing content for commercial gain without permission.</li>
      <li>Scraping or automated misuse that degrades service.</li>
      <li>Misrepresenting content as official AWS material.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      Content is provided by the author and may be formatted or rewritten with AI, which can introduce errors.
      If you spot inaccuracies, please submit a pull request via the GitHub link in the footer.
    </p>

    <h2>Exam Integrity</h2>
    <p>
      Do not post or share actual AWS exam questions or recalled items. This site is for strengthening AWS concepts,
      terminology, and use-case judgment only.
    </p>
    <p>
      Any similarity between the practice questions here and real exam questions is purely coincidental.
      If something appears similar, it is accidental or the result of common architectural patterns.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>We are not liable for losses arising from use of this site. Use at your own risk.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
